To install [35;1mPenguin[0m, you must be connected to the internet!

For Wi-Fi, authenticate to the wireless network using the [32miwctl[0m utility.
Ethernet and Wi-Fi connections using DHCP should work automatically.

You can start the installation by first editting, then running the [32mchinstrap.zsh[0m script
in the current directory. You can also follow the [38;2;23;147;209mArch Linux[0m installation guide at
https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Installation_guide. Remember to [32mpacstrap[0m the
[35;1mpenguin-defaults[0m package to install the full [35;1mPenguin[0m desktop.

After connecting to the internet, the installation guide can be accessed
via the convenience script [32mInstallation_guide[0m.

